title: Kudrat
subTitle: When Chandramukhi visits Shimla, she realises that she was Paro, a girl who is raped and murdered, in her previous life. Thereafter, she decides to punish her culprits and get justice.

title: Chitchor
subTitle: When Geeta's sister arranges her wedding with a young engineer, their father mistakenly brings the wrong man home. However, as love blossoms between the two, the arrival of a letter startles everyone.

title: My Life My Story
subTitle: The host invites prominent Bollywood celebrities who open up about their personal life and share interesting anecdotes based on their experiences.

title: Locket
subTitle: In a majestic kingdom, the treacherous relative of a king plots to seize the throne. However, his path is blocked by the crown prince, whose locket holds the key to a hidden treasure.

title: Upkar
subTitle: Radha's elder son sacrifices his ambitions to ensure his brother Puran gets a good education. Despite this, Puran grows up to become a ruthless man.

subTitle: Upon his release from exile, Ashok's life turns upside down when he learns about his mother's death and the truth behind his false accusation.

title: Mawaali
subTitle: Ramesh works for an industrialist and falls in love with his daughter. However, things take a turn when the industrialist is murdered and Ramesh is arrested for the crime.

title: Humshakal
subTitle: Ram, a poor labourer, marries Radha. One day, when their child is seriously ill, Radha arrives at her husband's place of work and is shocked to see that he is leading a dual life with another woman.

subTitle: Sanga, a devout employee of Raja Laxman Singh, is falsely accused of killing him. He escapes prison and forms a group of revolutionaries with the sole aim of driving the British out of India.

title: Saathi
subTitle: Ravi marries Shanti, leaving Rajni heartbroken. Unfortunately, Shanti develops a dreaded disease and runs away as she does not want to be a burden on Ravi.

title: Anita

title: Batwara

title: Dosti
subTitle: A series of unfortunate events causes Ramu, a young boy, to lose his parents and his legs. He is befriended by Mohan, a boy with visual impairment, and they team up to survive on the streets.
